relation to joining the Adventurer's Guild.

Guild Master Agonia: You need to pass a rigorous
examination. Do you truly have the determination and will
for it?

Girl Ect: I have a dream. This dream is a dream shared by me
and Papa.
Girl Ect: Please, I'm begging you!

Clea: It seems that she has quite a lot of knowledge.
Wouldn't someone with talent like hers be necessary in the
Adventurer's Guild?

Guild Master Agonia: Understood. Since there is a
recommendation from a regular member, let's conduct a
thorough examination.

Guild Master Agonia: However, you are still recovering from
your illness, so first, please focus on resting and
recovering.

Girl Ect: Yes, understood! Thank you very much, Agonia-san,
Clea-san!

Girl Ect: I will definitely join the guild! Not only for my
own dream, but also to be of help to everyone!

Guild Master Agonia: Considering Melos' will, I wanted to
protect Ect in a safe manner...

Clea: I'm sorry, but Ect reminds me of my past self at that
time.
Guild Master Agonia: I also remembered you.

Stolge the Merciful: Hahaha, adventurers are called
adventurers because they live by the belief that being an
adventurer is not just a title!

Stolge the Merciful: Sooner or later, Ect was aiming to
become an adventurer.
Guild Master Agonia: You're so carefree, honestly...

Stolge the Merciful: We adults will take care of the
troublesome things. It might be better than having
investigations and adventures done without permission,
right?

Guild Master Agonia: Let's conduct the entrance exam at the
appropriate time. At that time, I will also ask for Clea and
the others' cooperation.
Clea: Of course, since I recommended her.

Guild Master Agonia: Please continue the investigation of
the Rakio Ruins. I will prepare a request letter as a
request from me.

events.name: わんぱく少女の冒険/ドラゴンの爪話しかけ
ドラゴンの爪自動実行

parameters:
General Atu: First, it's my turn... I'll ask for your
cooperation in subjugating the goblins in the Valier region.

General Atu: The court magicians believe that there is some
kind of powerful entity involved in the activation of the
goblins in the Valier region.
Clea: A massive power... a dragon!

General Atu: After hearing your story, I have come to that
conclusion. If that's the case, we can see the whereabouts
of the dragon.

General Atu: There is a high possibility that there is a
dragon near the area where the goblins are being activated!

General Atu: I have obtained information that the goblins
are moving towards the village of Lippi in Camps.
Clea: Understood... Leave it to me.

Playboy Noble Luid: Hmm... As expected of the general, most
of the information I investigated turned out to be the same.

Playboy Noble Luid: The village of Lippi is located in the
outskirts of Camps... It's a village situated close to the
Valier Mountains.

Playboy Noble Luid: Be careful, as that area is filled with
people who are quite twisted in their own ways!

General Atu: Camps is a complex place with a high number of
devil worshippers and also has issues with thieves.

Playboy Noble Luid: Be careful and take care! It's possible
that not only the goblins, but also other creatures might be
influenced by the dragon.
General Atu: ...What is your purpose for coming here?

Playboy Noble Luid: I'm a fan of Clea-chan, you know. She's
so cute, devoted, and... fragile.

General Atu: Hmph... I don't like you guys! Don't you dare
interfere with me and these guys, okay?

General Atu: Agonia, bring out the chessboard! Let's do
this!

Guild Leader Agonia: I don't mind... but are you sure it'll
be okay?

Guild Leader Agonia: Watching you play might not be very
enjoyable since you're not very good at using the queen.

Playboy Noble Luid: Don't worry! A young rascal like me will
hurry back home!

Playboy Noble Luid: Hahaha, please enjoy the game to the
fullest.

events.name: 王妃カロンへの謁見自動実行

parameters:
Guild Leader Agonia: There are still many things to discuss,
but I will take my leave for now.

Adventurer Rex: Long time no see... I'm really glad that
you're safe.
Adventurer Rex: Um... If I call for Sophia now--
Priestess Sophia: Mmm... Lord Rex... Mmm...
Priestess Sophia: Haa... haa... I-I'm sorry...!

Priestess Sophia: Since the day we parted, I have been
living while constantly thinking of you...

Priestess Sophia: I'm so happy that we were able to meet
like this again...
Adventurer Rex: Me too... I never forgot about you.
Adventurer Rex: From now on, together.

Priestess Sophia: Until now and from now on... I will fight
for you.

Priestess Sophia: I will definitely make you sit on the
throne.

Priestess Sophia: Let's have a discussion with the
Adventurer's Guild. It is essential for us to have them as
our fighting force.
Priestess Sophia: Let's go, Prince Rex.
Guild Leader Agonia: I have a question, Clea.
Guild Leader Agonia: Who are you?

Clea: I don't know. I was turned into a vengeful spirit by a
dragon.
Clea: Now that the dragon is dead, I am no longer anyone.
Guild Leader Agonia: I see, then--
Clea: However, I do want to become someone.

Clea: And I want the people who supported me when I became
someone to be happy.

Clea: Seeing the friends who came to help me made me feel
stronger.

Guild Leader Agonia: I have been disappointed with Clea's
recent attitude. I even thought that she was not suitable
for the Adventurer Guild, Futeira.

Guild Leader Agonia: What are the three principles of the
Adventurer Guild?
Clea: I won't betray, I won't lie, and I won't run away.

Clea: I have always believed that it should be like this,
now and in the future.

Guild Leader Agonia: By defeating the dragon, you have
brought many things to the Adventurer Guild.

Guild Leader Agonia: I have prepared two things in
recognition of your achievements.

Guild Leader Agonia: First of all, I will promote you.
Please continue to fulfill requests with renewed
determination from now on.

Guild Leader Agonia: And this is the mantle. It is a symbol
of a high-ranking position in the Adventurer Guild.

Guild Leader Agonia: I want you to carry the Adventurer
Guild and its oath more than ever before.
Clea: Yes, thank you very much.

Celis of the Swift Wind: It's been a while... I'm glad to
see that you're looking better.
Clea: I'm sorry for causing you worry.
Celis of the Swift Wind: Hehe, I'll put the mantle on you.
Clea: Yes, thank you very much!
Celis of the Swift Wind: Guild Leader.
Guild Leader Agonia: Yes, what can I do for you?

Celis of the Swift Wind: Please leave because the girls are
changing clothes.

Guild Leader Agonia: So, you're just going to put on the
mantle, right?
Celis of the Swift Wind: Please hurry.
Guild Leader Agonia: Sigh... I understand.

Guild Leader Agonia: I see... So the Imperial Dark Division
Ishekel has started to move.

Guild Leader Agonia: And the production of dragons by Court
Magician Eramota...

Guild Leader Agonia: It's an unbelievable story, but we can
consider it all to be true.

Stolge the Merciful: I didn't tell Clea and the others, but
I was protecting and escorting the rescued Lex.

Stolge the Merciful: Although I wanted to remain neutral as
a guild, there were various complicated circumstances.
Clea: I was rescued... Was someone holding me captive?

Priestess Sophia: Queen Caron... She was holding Lord Lex
captive to maintain her power.

Priestess Sophia: This is a power struggle over the imperial
throne... It's divided between the Prince faction supporting
Lord Lex and the Queen faction supporting Queen Caron.

Priestess Sophia: My only wish is for you to join the Prince
faction in the Adventurer's Guild.

Guild Leader Agonia: Our answer remains the same as before.
The Adventurer's Guild does not belong to any faction.

Guild Leader Agonia: This is an order from the previous
Adventurer's Guild Leader. We should only align ourselves
when neutrality itself is threatened.

Stolge the Merciful: I think we talked about it when we met
here, but you know that Lex himself has no intention of
becoming king, right?

Stolge the Merciful: The prince who has no intention of
becoming king... We cannot make that man the king of the
empire.

Priestess Sophia: I'm sorry for asking too much, Clea-chan,
and for dragging you into this.

Stolge the Merciful: I don't know the reason why it's
important to keep an eye on Sophia, but I'm willing to do
anything for Lex.
Clea: Of course, Sophia-san is an important comrade to us.

Guild Leader Agonia: The movements in the royal palace have
become tumultuous. We will also take action, so please be
careful.

Guild Leader Agonia: The fact that they have even reached
the shadowy parts means that the enemy is no longer choosing
their methods.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
実績 罪深きアリシア
アゴニアのイベントページがいっぱいなので自動実行

Guild Leader Agonia: It seems that there is a commotion
around the royal palace. Please explain in detail what
happened.
Clea: Understood. I will convey what I saw and heard.

Stolge the Merciful: To have assassinated Lady Pilia...
Honestly, I must say this is beyond what I expected.

Fuchiyo no Shimosu: Isn't it a bad story that the intention
to seriously go after the throne has been conveyed both
internally and externally?

Fuchiyo no Shimosu: In the end, there's no other way but to
resort to killing each other.

Celis of the Swift Wind: But it's not a commendable way to
do it.

Guild Leader Agonia: Please stay by Prince Rex's side as
much as possible... He is still a vulnerable presence...
even for the Prince's faction.

Guild Leader Agonia: For us, the Adventurer's Guild as
well...

Clea: Understood. I will take care of the request from
Prince Rex.

Guild Leader Agonia: I don't particularly like old
stories... but it feels like it was just yesterday when you
knocked on the gate saying you wanted to become an
adventurer.

Guild Leader Agonia: You have defeated a dragon and now bear
the mantle of the symbol of the Adventurer's Guild.

Guild Leader Agonia: I would like to promote Clea. Is there
any objection as someone who also bears the mantle?

Celis of the Swift Wind: I believe I am suitable. Clea has
grown into an indispensable presence in the Adventurer's
Guild.

Stolge the Merciful: I also agree. Clea has brought many
things to the Adventurer's Guild.

Fuchiyo no Shimosu: I don't care if you agree or not, but in
this situation, it would be better to have more high-
ranking members who can contribute to the battle, right?
Celis of the Swift Wind: ...You're not being honest.
Fuchiyo no Shimosu: What did you say!?

Guild Leader Agonia: This is not the end. I expect further
achievements and further growth.
Clea: I won't betray, lie, or run away.

Clea: From now on, I swear to wield my greatsword for the
sake of the Adventurer's Guild Futeira and for the sake of
my comrades.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Guild Leader Agonia: I didn't expect you to come from your
side.

General Atu: It seems that Lex has made up his mind to
become the king, just as a way to distract himself.
Guild Leader Agonia: Yes, I have heard it directly from him.

General Atu: So the Adventurer's Guild sided with Lex,
considering that you all inherited it, it's a natural
decision.

Guild Leader Agonia: As expected, I didn't make an immediate
decision like you did in chess. I took my time and made a
thoughtful decision.

Guild Leader Agonia: Well, with this move of not using the
Queen, you will checkmate.

General Atu: I see, I see. If you take the same amount of
time to think as I do, that would be considered a [mistake].
Guild Leader Agonia: Moved the Queen...

Guild Leader Agonia: Are you siding with Caron, is that what
you're saying?
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Guild Leader Agonia: ...May I ask for the reason?
General Atu: Agonia, this chess game is not over yet.

General Atu: Let's continue this discussion on the
battlefield, not on the chessboard.
Guild Leader Agonia: ...Fighting against Atu, huh?
Guild Leader Agonia: We'll need a different strategy.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
アゴニアのEVページが多いため自動実行で仮置き

Guild Leader Agonia: I have heard the story from Prince
Lex's messenger. The other guild members are also making
their final preparations.
Guild Leader Agonia: Are the preparations complete?

Guild Leader Agonia: The movements on Caron's side have
become more active. Please understand that time is running
out.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

\CL After completing the quest directive Report to Guild
Leader Agonia, you will no longer be able to freely accept,
progress, or complete quests in the future.
\CL Are you sure you want to complete the quest directive?
Clea: Don't worry, the preparations are complete.

Guild Leader Agonia: Who are you? I have asked you the same
question multiple times.

Guild Leader Agonia: This request has the potential to
change the future of the empire. There may be something that
becomes visible within this request.

Guild Leader Agonia: I am looking forward to seeing what
kind of answer you will give.

Clea: I think if my father were alive, he would have spoken
like Mr. Agonia.
Clea: I couldn't help but laugh.

Guild Leader Agonia: Honestly... you're about the same age
as your grandfather.

Guild Leader Agonia: I will enter the final adjustments with
Atu. Clea, please escort Prince Rex to the guild.
Clea: Understood, I will definitely bring him back safely.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Guild Leader Agonia: I have heard the story from Prince
Lex's messenger. The other guild members are also making
their final preparations.

Guild Leader Agonia: Have you finished gathering your
forces?

Guild Leader Agonia: The movements on Caron's side have
become more active. Please understand that time is running
out.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

\CL After completing the quest Report to Guild Leader
Agonia, you will no longer be able to freely accept,

Clea: There's no problem. Many reliable people are willing
to cooperate.

Guild Leader Agonia: Who are you? I have asked you the same
question multiple times.

Guild Leader Agonia: Do you think you can obtain that
answer?

Clea: However, from the time we defeated the dragon until
today...

Clea: Every time I take on a request, I feel like I'm
starting to see the answer that I should come up with
myself.

Guild Leader Agonia: Is that so? Perhaps you are starting to
grasp something.

Guild Leader Agonia: A girl who wields a sword that is too
big for her own stature, driven by nothing but a desire for
revenge. That was my first impression of you when we spoke
in this place.

Guild Leader Agonia: I have become excited to see your
growth, even though you stumble along the way.

Guild Leader Agonia: This request is extremely important. It
will determine the survival of the Adventurer's Guild.
Clea: Yes, I believe I understand.

Guild Leader Agonia: No matter what happens, the
Adventurer's Guild, Futera, exists to protect the daily
lives of others.

Guild Leader Agonia: Please continue to show me your growth
in the days to come.

Clea: I think if my father were alive, he would have spoken
like Mr. Agonia.
Clea: I couldn't help but laugh.

Guild Leader Agonia: Honestly... you're about the same age
as your grandfather.

Guild Leader Agonia: I will enter the final adjustments with
Atu. Clea, please escort Prince Rex to the guild.
Clea: Understood, I will definitely bring him back safely.
Guild Leader Agonia: Your father, you say?
